cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on Network Function Virtualization (NFV) and its impact on network operators, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a novel column-generation model for placing multiple VNF SCs and routing, which involves control and optimization of network resources. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the feasibility of a distributed NFVI and its impact on network-resource consumption, which falls under the domain of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper addresses the computationally-complex problem of multiple VNF SC placement and routing, which involves computational complexity. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper proposes a model for placing and routing VNF SCs, which involves programming and implementation of the model.
